---
import Eyebrow from '../primitives/Eyebrow.astro';

// How recognition works: verbatim explainer paragraph only. The standalone four-rung
// label ladder was REMOVED per the Codex source-of-truth audit: the recognition lock
// (01.02 Recognition Thresholds (Decision), "What this locks for the Phase 2 PRD")
// requires a short, jargon-free on-screen explanation wherever Member / Active Member /
// Ambassador / Leadership Circle appear as labels, and the vault supplies no such hint
// copy. The level names remain ONLY inline within this contextualised sentence. Gold
// (recognition-only) therefore has no vault-sourced element to attach to here, so it is
// correctly absent from this page.
---
<section class="mbr-recognition" id="recognition" aria-labelledby="rec-h">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="head reveal">
      <Eyebrow onPaper>How recognition works</Eyebrow>
      <h2 id="rec-h">How recognition works</h2>
    </div>
    <p class="rec-body reveal" style="--i:1">As you take part, host, mentor, and help others, you earn standing in the community, from Member to Active Member to Ambassador, and a small Leadership Circle at the top. Standing is earned only by contribution, never bought, because we handle no money. It is how we say thank you, and how members supporting members becomes the engine that grows WAI-ME.</p>
  </div>
</section>
